docs.lead_paragraph: In the twelve months ended on April 1 exports by the United States to the sixteen trade-agreement countries increased 68.6 per cent over the average for the calendar years 1934 and 1935, compared with an increase of only 50.5 per cent in the export trade with non-agreement countries, the Department of Commerce reported today.
